{
  "stem": "7093.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "And as I was standing there with a flag singing, the Hatik-- leading the singing of the Hatikvah, the police came in and took us all to the police headquarters and kept us for an hour.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "I must say, we thought it was rather a joke.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "But this was my first encounter with the police as a Jew, as a Zionist.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I suppose so.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't remember, really.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The only thing I remember that we were taken there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then I don't know why they let us go again.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The rest was-- well, as I say, at the age of 18 in 1942, I went up and did this course, this nursery school course.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When I finished, then the head of the nursery-- of the training college sent me out into various jobs, always about six weeks, two months.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I spent the next year like that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she constantly changed my job.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I had lots of trouble with my father about it because he said, you are lazy.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You are not-- you don't-- you can't keep a job.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it wasn't at all that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because eventually, I was then chosen in '44, January, I was chosen to become the assistant nursery school teacher at the training at the model nursery of the training college, of which I was incredibly proud.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I was very, very pleased.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Unfortunately, not much came of it because this was January, 1944.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I also got ill then.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I had a funny illness that turned out I had a-- I had to have a big operation.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Anyway, I-- on the 19th of March 1944, the Germans marched in, and we were occupied.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not-- I don't know whether it necessarily from the Austrians from what was going on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Hungarian were anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
